						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the meadow called ‘Kundāṇi-Belūr-Jeḍḍu’.</p>						

						<p>This record in charcters of about the 14th century, seems to refer to a grant to the god (?) Paṭṇa-voḍeya, by <hi rend="bold">Āḷpēndra-dēva</hi> (name not given), his ministers and the <hi rend="italic">Thousand</hi> of the village. </p>						

